paragraph.value: The experimental results on WOZ 2.0 corpus are presented in Table 1. The three baseline models, BERT+RNN, BERT+RNN+Ontology, and the slot-dependent SUMBT, showed no performance differences. On the other hand, the slot-independent SUMBT which learned the shared information from all across domains and slots significantly outperformed those baselines, resulting in
joint accuracy. The proposed model achieved

performance in both WOZ 2.0 and MultiWOZ datasets.
